{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"9eb510892d1accc0c715d21128d216b2e6f74967"},"timestamp":1587833625,"title":"(core) Rendertarget does not update mipmaps","message":"This is a quality problem that comes with rendertarget updates. While,\non creation, the backing store will generate mipmaps - they will not be\nre-generated when the color attachment is updated.\n\nRelatedly, image_as_frame could/should be used to manually provide different\nmipmap levels so that we can use our own mipmaping algorithms as well as open\nup for other intermediate tricks.","files":null}]}